record.text: This doesn’t mean you shouldn’t have a plot in mind, but you have to keep in mind the steps necessary for your characters to reach whatever point you want them to, and adjust as necessary. And sometimes that may mean realizing that as they are, they wouldn’t move the plot you have in mind.

The reason I don’t write detailed plots has a lot to do with this, actually. If you’re too beholden to the story you’re often tempted to force the characters to do things in order to get where you need, when the characters should be moving the plot most of the time.
